03/07/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Non-permanent Security Council member Greece took over the Council's presidency for one month on Friday (1 July).
Greek Foreign Minister Petros Molyviatis told reporters that his country was ready and able to meet the challenges related to the post.
He outlined the Middle East, East Africa, terrorism and peacekeeping force maintenance as priorities.
(Kathimerini, ANA - 02/07/01)
